"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-09-paris-2024-olympics-amusan-crashes-out-in-womens-100m-hurdles\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's hope of winning a medal at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games was further dashed after Tobi Amusan failed to secure a place in the final of the women's 100m hurdles.  Amusan finished third in the semi-final missing out on automatic qualification.  The 27-year-old also finished 9th overall in the final standings.  The world record holder was one of the favourites to win gold medal in the event.  The Ogun-State born athlete made it to the final three years in Tokyo.  She is however still looking for her first medal in the Olympics.  EPL: Gallas predicts position Chelsea will finish under Maresca  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria disqualified from men's 4x400m relay final  2025 World Championships: Amusan credits 'God' for silver medal success  Amusan confirms for Diamond League season opener  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"